e.com/artists/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰 (Elton John)</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/arctic-monkeys">北极猴子 (Arctic Monkeys)</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/guns-n-roses">枪炮玫瑰 (Guns N&#39; Roses)</a>的表演。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/skepta-is-searching-for-actor-to-play-young-skepta-3516540">《Skepta 正在寻找一位演员在一个项目中扮演“年轻的 Skepta”》一文</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
 《城市：天际线 2》不会使用 Steam 创意工坊进行模组https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/cities-skylines-2-will-not-use-steam-workshop-for-mods-3516501?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=cities-skylines-2-不会使用 Steam 创意工坊进行模组Imogen DonovanTue, 17 Oct 2023 14:29:53 +0000 Gaming NewsNewsPCPS5Xbox Series X|Shttps://www.nme.com/?p=3516501 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这有利于所有玩家的“包容性”体验</p><p>帖子<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/cities-skylines-2-will-not-use-steam-workshop-for-mods-3516501">“城市：天际线 2”将不会使用 Steam 创意工坊来制作</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上的模组。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>发行商<a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/paradox-interactive">Paradox Interactive</a>透露， <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/cities-skylines-2"><em>《城市：天际线 2》</em></a>将不会使用 Steam 创意工坊来支持其模组。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/gaming-features/the-mountain-goats-john-darnielle-talks-magic-the-gathering-secret-lair-set-3483851">山羊乐队的约翰·达尼尔 (John Darnielle) 谈论为《万智牌》写预言</a></strong></li></ul><p>相反，Paradox Mods 将成为<em>《城市：天际线 2》</em>创意方面的一站式商店。这将为<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/pc">PC</a>和主机玩家创造一种有凝聚力的体验，而不会让玩后者的玩家感到被前者的功能所排斥。</p><p> “其核心原因之一是它的包容性；修改功能将扩展到跨平台（PC 和游戏机）的玩家，这符合我们为尽可能多的人提供修改和享受游戏的机会的承诺，”发行商<a href="https://forum.paradoxplaza.com/forum/threads/updates-on-modding-and-performance-for-cities-skylines-ii.1601865/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">在其论坛的帖子中</a>解释道。 </p><figure id="attachment_3516529" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3516529" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3516529" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3516529" class="wp-caption-text"> 《城市天际线 2》图片来源：Paradox Interactive</figcaption></figure><p>发行商承认，在<em>《城市：天际线 2》</em>所有三个版本中完全集成资产模组的路线可能会导致玩家遇到一些初期问题。</p><p> “与所有重大更新一样，我们充分意识到它可能带来的学习曲线，但我们致力于提供资源以确保顺利过渡到 Paradox Mods，”它确认道。</p><p>此外，游戏内编辑器在发布时将是“基本”，但将继续“扩展和增强”，让玩家在他们的城市中发挥他们的想象力。</p><p> <em>《城市：天际线 2》</em>将于 10 月 24 日在 PC 和 PC Game Pass 上推出，但<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/ps5">PS5</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/xbox-series-xs">Xbox Series X|S</a>版本则<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/cities-skylines-2-has-been-delayed-for-xbox-and-ps5-3505927">推迟到 2024 年春季</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3516530" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3516530" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3516530" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cities-skylines-2-is-changing-mod-support-to-paradox-mods-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3516530" class="wp-caption-text"> 《城市天际线 2》图片来源：Paradox Interactive</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/colossal-order">Colossal Order</a>和 Paradox Interactive 在 9 月份表示：“我们已经意识到，我们需要更多的时间来达到我们设定的质量目标。” “额外的时间使我们能够专注于匹配所有平台的质量和性能。”</p><p>在其他游戏新闻中， <em>《Don’t Scream》</em>是一款<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/this-blair-witch-style-horror-game-can-only-be-completed-if-you-dont-scream-3516460">新发现的恐怖游戏，玩家如果想坚持到游戏结束，就不能尖叫，</a>无论游戏可能会向他们抛出什么。</p><p>帖子<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/cities-skylines-2-will-not-use-steam-workshop-for-mods-3516501">“城市：天际线 2”将不会使用 Steam 创意工坊来制作</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上的模组。</p> ;
安迪·伯纳姆（Andy Burnham）猛烈抨击“荒谬”的脱欧规则，并要求艺术家在欧洲“自由交流” https://www.nme.com/news/music/andy-burnham-slams-ridiculous-brexit-rules-demands-free-exchange-artists-through-europe-3515357?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=andy-burnham-猛烈抨击荒谬的英国脱欧规则，要求通过欧洲自由交换艺术家Elizabeth AubreyTue, 17 Oct 2023 14:21:38 +0000 Music NewsNewsBrexit https://www.nme.com/?p=3515357 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="安迪·伯纳姆" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>业界呼吁“解决”与欧洲的问题，指责政府“在工作中睡觉”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/andy-burnham-slams-ridiculous-brexit-rules-demands-free-exchange-artists-through-europe-3515357">安迪·伯纳姆 (Andy Burnham) 抨击“荒谬”的英国脱欧规则并要求艺术家在欧洲“自由交流”的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="安迪·伯纳姆" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Andy-Burnham-mayor-of-Manchester-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>曼彻斯特市长安迪·伯纳姆（Andy Burnham）猛烈抨击了英国脱欧后围绕艺术家前往欧洲巡演的“荒谬”规定，呼吁整个欧洲的音乐家“自由交流”。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li dir="auto"><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-uk-house-of-lords-2022-artist-crew-unemployment-europe-3315337">英国脱欧：英国政府警告音乐家和工作人员“可能会发现自己集体失业”</a></strong></li></ul><p>周五（10 月 13 日）曼彻斯特首届“<a href="https://beyondthemusic.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">超越音乐</a>”会议上，伯纳姆在讨论领导人如何齐心协力改变巡演音乐家的签证问题时表示，需要开展一场运动来表明情况有多“严重”。成为艺术家和场馆的共同选择。</p><p>早在 2021 年， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-industry-feel-theyve-been-dealt-a-no-deal-brexit-but-call-on-government-to-take-it-seriously-and-fix-it-2856716">英国音乐产业就公开表示，</a>当政府<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/government-rejects-visa-free-brexit-touring-petition-blames-eu-promises-help-navigate-changes-2875506">未能就音乐家和工作人员的免签证旅行和欧洲范围内的工作许可证进行谈判</a>时，他们实际上是如何遭遇“无协议脱欧”的。</p><p>结果，在<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/coronavirus">新冠疫情</a>之后，试图再次上路的艺术家们发现自己正走在英国脱欧后第一个夏天欧洲巡演的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-one-year-on-music-industry-remain-frustrated-at-clueless-government-3130861">预期“崎岖道路”</a>上——发现英国<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-europe-strangling-talent-carnets-visa-merch-crew-government-response-summer-2022-3288735">脱欧的复杂性正在“扼杀下一代英国人才”在摇篮里”</a> 。</p><p>在上议院举行的听证会上，英国脱欧已经对那些希望前往欧洲巡演的人造成了损害，随后政府被警告称， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-uk-house-of-lords-2022-artist-crew-unemployment-europe-3315337">音乐家和工作人员“可能会发现自己集体失业”</a> 。</p><p>伯纳姆与北方市长、西约克郡的特雷西·布拉宾和利物浦市地区的史蒂夫·罗瑟勒姆一起发表讲话，表示他们现在需要共同努力，创建一个允许音乐家在整个欧洲自由旅行的系统。</p><p> “我认为作为市长，我们需要自下而上地大力开展这项运动，表明这个行业对我们至关重要，而不是边缘化、关键性的，我们需要一种安排，允许从欧洲到这里巡演的音乐家自由交流对于进入欧洲的英国音乐家来说，”伯纳姆说。</p><p> “对我们来说，这对我们的游客经济绝对至关重要，而且对欧洲各地对我们城市地区的了解和了解也至关重要。这只是废话，不是吗？您必须了解<a href="https://travel-europe.europa.eu/etias_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ETIAS</a> [欧洲工作签证] 以及所有这些。如果我们允许这些东西继续存在，对我们造成的损害将远远超过我们对一个国家的了解。” </p><figure id="attachment_3515563" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3515563" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3515563" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty.jpg" alt="欧洲歌唱大赛冠军洛琳在利物浦" width="2000" height="1269" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty-1392x883.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Eurovision-winner-Loreen-in-Liverpool-CREDIT_-Getty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3515563" class="wp-caption-text">欧洲歌唱大赛冠军洛琳在利物浦 – 图片来源：Getty</figcaption></figure><p>利物浦市长罗瑟勒姆表示， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/eurovision-2023-what-will-be-the-long-term-impact-for-liverpool-and-its-music-scene-3441197">该市夏季举办的欧洲电视网</a>受到英国脱欧规定的影响，并导致“整个事情出现很多很多问题”，包括一些艺术家被拒绝入场。</p><p>然而，他接着声称“人们对此视而不见”，因为“全世界的目光都在注视着我们”，并表示“在一些无意义的事情上找到了解决办法”，并称这证明了这些问题可以通过更多人的参与来克服。向上思考。</p><p> “这一切都需要澄清，不是吗？我们需要真正找出问题，然后让某人一一说，‘好吧，这就是解决问题的方法。这就是你如何解决这个问题的。”</p><p>他接着问道：“我认为我说得对，有人向鲍里斯·约翰逊提出了解决这个问题的方案，但它被退回了？”伯纳姆对此回答道：“是的，它被退回欧洲了”，以回应<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ministers-reject-fighting-for-visa-free-brexit-touring-plan-for-musicians-2860053">前首相鲍里斯·约翰逊拒绝音乐家免签证巡演计划</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.vivalavisa.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visa La Visa</a>的安迪·科里根 (Andy Corrigan) 是一家帮助音乐家办理在欧洲工作签证的复杂流程的组织，他告诉专家组，职业生涯刚刚起步的音乐家“由于获得签证的实际成本和费用而推迟了巡演”。允许。”</p><p>他继续说道：“很多人害怕超出分配的天数，他们担心在某个时候他们会被抓住。也曾有人被抓过——几个月前在丹麦，一些视听技术人员被拘留并驱逐出丹麦。</p><p> “去年有报道称乐队因[签证流程]错误而被拒之门外。这让音乐家们不再去旅行。” </p><figure id="attachment_3515364" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3515364" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3515364" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2.jpg" alt="Brexit conference at Beyond the Music" width="2000" height="1272" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2-800x509.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2-696x443.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2-1392x885.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-music-2-1068x679.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3515364" class="wp-caption-text"> (LR) Jon Collins, Andy Corrigan, Rob Challice, Andy Burnham, Tracy Brabin, Steve Rotherham – CREDIT: Ella Peck</figcaption></figure><p> In <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/wolf-alice-joff-oddie-post-brexit-touring-op-ed-3288762">an op-ed message penned for <em>NME</em></a> last summer, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/wolf-alice">Wolf Alice</a> guitarist Joff Oddie wrote of his fears that changes brought about by Brexit were “going to seriously damage the prospects of so many new acts, who have already been held back by two years of not being able to tour due to the pandemic”.</p><p> “We cannot expect to retain our rich musical culture and heritage if we fail to support both upcoming and established artists,” wrote Oddie. “We need a new deal for touring from the Government now. It is time to tear down the barriers artists are facing touring the EU. It is time to let the music move!”</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE:</strong> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-europe-strangling-talent-carnets-visa-merch-crew-government-response-summer-2022-3288735">Brexit is “strangling the next generation of UK talent in the cradle” in return to touring</a></li></ul><p> At the conference, Brabin also brought up the difficulty that some musicians in her region had experienced trying to sell merchandise in Europe because of issues with complex VAT rules since Brexit, including charges for taking merchandise into and out of different countries.</p><p> “A lot of young people are telling me part of the problem is merchandise and they can&#39;t take their t-shirts and all their stuff [to sell] in because it costs too much money – but that&#39;s the only way they&#39;re making money in the first place.”</p><p> Corrigan went on to say the current rules “don&#39;t work” and need simplifying to help bands earn money in Europe once again.</p><p> A new report <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/almost-50-per-cent-of-uk-musicians-working-less-in-europe-after-brexit-3487189">recently showed that almost 50 per cent of UK musicians are working less in Europe since Brexit.</a> The new Paying The Price report from the Independent Society of Musicians, surveyed over 400 musicians and found that 47.4 per cent of those surveyed said they had worked less in the EU after Brexit went through, with 27.8 per cent having no work on the continent at all.</p><p> 40 per cent had work cancelled since January 1 2021, with almost as many (39 per cent) having to turn down planned work.</p><p> Independent Society of Musicians boss Deborah Annetts said of the findings: “The government has been asleep on the job. It could have tackled many of the issues facing the music sector by itself and made Brexit work. It chose not to. This report provides a pathway to make Brexit work for music, and most of the recommendations would not require renegotiating the TCA.”</p><p> She added: “Brexit should never have meant that musicians cannot share their talent freely with our closest neighbours. This damages our country, our soft power and our precious creative talent pipeline. Music is worth £5.8billion to the UK economy and the wider creative industries are worth £116billion. We call on the government to take action and make Brexit work for the wellbeing of musicians and our economy.” </p><figure id="attachment_3515363" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3515363" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3515363" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1.jpg" alt="Brexit conference" width="2000" height="1268" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1-800x507.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1-696x441.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1-1392x883.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Mayors-Panel-Beyond-the-Music-1-1068x677.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3515363" class="wp-caption-text"> Mayor&#39;s Panel at Beyond the Music in Manchester – CREDIT: Ella Peck</figcaption></figure><p> Rotherham said in terms of negotiating with the treasury, only by telling the government how much the UK economy is losing in real terms through the rules will it make any difference.</p><p> “A great thing about <a href="https://www.ukmusic.org/research-reports/here-there-and-everywhere/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UK Music is that they did a report</a> which showed how much UK Plc benefits from music. With [the] treasury, it&#39;s no good arguing the moral or ethical dimension of this. It&#39;s always about pound notes and that&#39;s what we need to do now. The country is actually losing out because of some of these restrictions.”</p><p> Burnham also added that it was time for ministers to stop evading questions around Brexit.</p><p> “We&#39;ve got to stop this idea that you can&#39;t raise things with ministers. It&#39;s just absolutely ridiculous,” he said in response to the government being reluctant to discussing to negotiate or discuss the issues many face post-Brexit.</p><p> “I think that the thing that really comes over to me is in this post-Brexit period when we should be trying to sort of promote positive images of Britain abroad, music&#39;s our best way of doing it…it shows Britain in a good way that people relate to. [But] it is…being denied to us because of these ridiculous rules around British musicians traveling into Europe.”</p><p> Burnham added: “I think the mayors can really be a voice for the industry…let&#39;s really move beyond this sort of period that we&#39;ve been in, this political sort of dead zone post-Brexit. Let&#39;s start calling out clearly what really is not working here in the interest of the country and start reaching out to [our] colleagues in Europe to get it fixed.”</p><p> The Beyond The Music conference also saw a panel hear how <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grassroots-venues-need-action-not-kind-words-as-they-had-for-disaster-without-arena-investment-3515347">grassroots venues need “action not kind words</a> ” as they had for “disaster” without investment from larger arenas and government attention.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/andy-burnham-slams-ridiculous-brexit-rules-demands-free-exchange-artists-through-europe-3515357">Andy Burnham slams “ridiculous” Brexit rules and demands “free exchange” of artists through Europe</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 Blu DeTiger 与 Mallrat 合作推出新单曲《Cut Me Down》 https://www.nme.com/news/music/blu-detiger-teams-up-with-mallrat-on-new-single-cut-me-down-3516503?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=blu-detiger-与 Mallrat 合作开发新单曲《cut-me-down》Anagricel Duran Tue, 17 Oct 2023 14:14:59 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndiePophttps://www.nme.com/?p=3516503 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Blu DeTiger 和 Mallrat。图片来源：Leon Bennett 和 Marc Grimwade" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “这首歌对我来说是一个很好的演变，也是我的另一面，人们还没有听过”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blu-detiger-teams-up-with-mallrat-on-new-single-cut-me-down-3516503">Blu DeTiger 与 Mallrat 合作制作的新单曲《Cut Me Down》</a>首先在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上发布。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Blu DeTiger 和 Mallrat。图片来源：Leon Bennett 和 Marc Grimwade" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Blu-DeTiger-and-Mallrat-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/blu-detiger">Blu DeTiger</a>与澳大利亚音乐家<a href="/artists/mallrat">Mallrat</a>联手制作了她的新单曲“Cut Me Down”——请听下面的内容。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/meet-the-artists-c23-blu-detiger-3399696">认识艺术家：Blu DeTiger</a></strong></li></ul><p>在这首歌中，DeTiger 和 Mallrat（真名 Grace Shaw）在人声和节奏上进行了权衡。 <em>“每次你砍倒我/我知道你下车了/以为你得到了/我现在完全不正常了/这很悲伤但很有趣/你继续尝试，”两人在面对那些人时合唱道。</em>享受砍倒别人的乐趣。</p><p> 《Cut Me Down》由 DeTiger、John Hill（ <a href="/artists/foals">Foals</a> 、 <a href="/artists/oliver-tree">Oliver Tree</a> ）和 Same Homaee（ <a href="/artists/selena-gomez">Selena Gomez</a> 、 <a href="/artists/dominic-fike">Dominic Fike</a> ）制作。这首歌是由三人在 Shaw 和 Amy Allen（ <a href="/artists/harry-styles">Harry Styles</a> 、 <a href="/artists/niall-horan">Niall Horan</a> 、 <a href="/artists/justin-bieber">Justin Bieber</a> ）的帮助下创作的。该曲目由 Detiger 担任贝斯手。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Blu DeTiger、Mallrat - Cut Me Down（展示台）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ndotYRhDk9M?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “《Cut Me Down》是一首自言自语的赞歌——提醒自己不要让别人打倒我。这是一首时髦而悲伤的波普音乐。我觉得这首歌对我来说是一个很好的演变，也是我的另一面，人们还没有听过，但充满灵魂的和弦和低音线的运动将它锚定在 Blu DeTiger 的声音中。这是我写过的最优美动人的低音部分之一，它以一种非常酷的方式跟随和支持人声。” DeTiger 谈到这首歌时说道（根据<a href="https://www.udiscovermusic.com/news/blu-detiger-mallrat-cut-me-down/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>udiscovermusic</em></a> ）。</p><p>她继续说道：“高亢的歌声就像我的高等天使在对我说话，他们带着勇气、态度和超然的态度来做这件事。我还和我的好朋友 Mallrat 合作创作了这首歌。我长期以来一直是她的粉丝——我喜欢她的语气、流畅度和声音中的性格。我认为它非常适合并提升了这首歌。”</p><p>这首歌是继之前的单曲《Elevator》和《Lipstick》之后，这两首单曲是<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/bose-x-nme-c23-track-by-track-3414044"><em>NME</em> x Bose 的 C23 Mixtape</a>的一部分。</p><p>谈到这首歌曲， <em>NME</em>表示：《Lipstick》证明了她的原创音乐为何同样出色：流畅的贝斯线和俏皮的律动为这首充满自信的歌曲增添了深情的氛围。最好的一点：Blu 古怪而直接的说唱方式始终引人入胜。这是一位想要坚定地保持自己的艺术家的声音——还有什么比这更酷的呢？”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/blu-detiger-teams-up-with-mallrat-on-new-single-cut-me-down-3516503">Blu DeTiger 与 Mallrat 合作制作的新单曲《Cut Me Down》</a>首先在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上发布。</p> ;
